text: The Eyre Developmental Road is a gazetted road in south-west Queensland that runs from Bedourie to Birdsville and then to the border with South Australia, where it continues as the Birdsville Track.Queensland Government - Department of Transport and Main Roads - Maps At the northern end it joins the Diamantina Developmental Road, and the mostly unsealed road crosses the Georgina River and Diamantina River. Maintenance of the road is the responsibility of the Queensland State Government. The Road has no major intersections. ==References== Category:Roads in Queensland Category:Highways in Queensland
title: Eyre Developmental Road
